      "content": "It sounds incredibly painful to feel that your love has come to seem like a burden, especially after years of giving. Please remember that by caring for yourself, you are actually making room for your family to attach to each other and care for one another again. Your desire to ease their struggle is a testament to your deep love, even if it feels like you are taking up space that could be otherwise used for joy. Reaching out for a temporary respite or support team could help your family enjoy moments without the weight of constant caregiving.",
